+# SDF label background icon
+
+Generated file:
+
+- `label-bubble-sdf.png` (128x64 RGBA SDF)
+
+Use in a MapLibre symbol layer as `icon-image` with `icon-text-fit`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "type": "symbol",
+  "layout": {
+    "icon-image": "label-bubble-sdf",
+    "icon-text-fit": "both",
+    "icon-text-fit-padding": [4, 8, 4, 8],
+    "text-field": ["coalesce", ["get", "alt_name"], ""],
+    "text-font": ["Open-Sans-Regular"]
+  },
+  "paint": {
+    "icon-color": "#ffffff",
+    "icon-halo-color": "#1f2937",
+    "icon-halo-width": 1,
+    "text-color": "#111111"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Regenerate with:
+
+```bash
+python3 scripts/generate_sdf_icon.py
+```
+
+The sprite pipeline (`scripts/run_sprite_pipeline.sh`) automatically copies all
+`assets/sprites/sdf/*.png` files into the combined `oe5ith-markers` sprite
+group. Icons with names ending in `-sdf` are flagged with `"sdf": true` in the
+generated sprite JSON.
EOF
)
